    "body": "\r\nfixed issue: #36853\r\nThis is my first time opening PR here so advice and change all welcome :)\r\n\r\n## Problems\r\nwhen using neovim to run/execute lua file (`nvim -l <file.lua>`), it will print an additional trailing newline via `msg_putchar('\\n')` after the script run. Inside `msg_putchar` on `msg_puts_printf` it will performs conversion from LF to CRLF.\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\nThe solution on this pr is adding a new globals called `msg_use_crlf` which default to true and will be set to false when on `-l` code path. Inside the `msg_puts_printf` function there is a new check if `msg_use_crlf == true` that will skip the CRLF conversion like setting `info_message` to true do.\r\n\r\nThe other way i try that i am not sure about is setting `info_message` to true but that will stream all the output into stdout instead of the current one which is stderr.",
    "closed_at": null,
