            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "can we avoid a new global, by checking `silent_mode` and/or `headless_mode` perhaps? https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/2368a9edbd6c4ac75dc2cb9471d1e2e93b5fdd18/src/nvim/main.c#L1388-L1390\n\nI don't really think headless mode needs CRLF, nor `nvim -es` etc. WDYT @luukvbaal @zeertzjq ",
            "commit_id": "170fe2ddb6c52a958456d40bc8e97b3e4cd65d1c",
            "created_at": "2026-02-28T12:23:34Z",
            "diff_hunk": "@@ -2905,7 +2905,7 @@ static void msg_puts_printf(const char *str, const ptrdiff_t maxlen)\n     if (!(silent_mode && p_verbose == 0)) {\n       // NL --> CR NL translation (for Unix, not for \"--version\")\n       p = &buf[0];\n-      if (*s == '\\n' && !info_message) {\n+      if (*s == '\\n' && !info_message && msg_use_crlf) {",
